subSubSection.paragraph:
This species is similar to 
Phyllocoptruta clematoclethra
Xue, Song & Hong, 2010, from 
Clematoclethra
sp. Maxim. (
Actinidiaceae
), but can be differentiated from the latter by admedian lines connected posteriorly (admedian lines separate in 
Phyllocoptruta clematoclethra
), scapular tubercles ahead of rear shield margin, scapular setae 16-18 (scapular tubercles on rear shield margin, scapular setae 3-4 in 
Phyllocoptruta clematoclethra
), female genital coverflap with 3 transverse basal lines (coverflap without transverse lines in 
Phyllocoptruta clematoclethra
) and 8-rayed empodium (5-rayed empodium in 
Phyllocoptruta clematoclethra
).
